Pre-Game Insights: South Africa are unbeaten at the tournament and have won matches when both setting targets and chasing but have faced tough competition from Associates.

England have settled into the tournament after a shaky start and have played and lost to their biggest rivals, Australia, but have won against Oman and Namibia to secure their place in the Super Eights.
South Africa humbled England at the 2023 ODI World Cup and have a chance to stamp their authority on this event.
South Africa have not faced consistent and genuine pace until now, which makes Jofra Archer an interesting opponent.
England's net-run-rate is currently at 1.34, putting them in a good position for the semi-finals.
South Africa's next challenge is to maintain their winning start against two former champions, while England aim to improve their performance and potentially reach the semi-finals.
Anrich Nortje is two wickets away from 50 in T20Is and Tabraiz Shamsi one away from 300 in all T20s.
Jos Buttler needs 19 more runs to become the ninth batter to 1,000 in all T20s this year.
